  "description": "<a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p1092331/\"><img src=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/2009/images/rss_shuangyu.gif\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a><br /><p>\n\t<img src=\"http://n1image.hjfile.cn/mh/2017/03/20/e3375ce701fac61956bdfc1c6b26e71d.jpg\" /></p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>How should you prepare for a job interview?如何为求职面试做准备？</strong></p>\n<p>\n\t<strong style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">英语君导读：求职面试到底该做什么准备？面试的时候应该说什么？还有，面试到底是怎样一回事？这个问题对于学生到和职场新手来说都是个老大难，英语君今天特地从quora给大家筛选了一篇高质量、篇幅短的回答，一起来看看吧~</strong></p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 25.2px;\">\n\t<a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p1092331\" title=\"点击获得更好的阅读体验\"><img src=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/2009/images/rss_video.gif\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 25.2px;\">\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 25.2px;\">本文声优：FISH</span></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 25.2px;\">\n\t<strong style=\"line-height: 25.2px;\">你</strong><strong style=\"line-height: 25.2px;\">想拥有和声优一样的流利口语吗？戳这里&gt;&gt;&gt;<a href=\"http://class.hujiang.com/classzt/MKTTopic_p92121?ch_source=ipo_en_0_rw&amp;editorid=be388e8c\" target=\"_blank\">体验外教1对1口语</a></strong></p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>获得807.9k 的好评回答@Adam Seabrook:</strong></p>\n<p>\n\tYou literally have 30 seconds to make an <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"https://dict.hjenglish.com/w/impression\" target=\"_blank\">impression</a> during an interview. This question should really be &quot;how do I <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"https://dict.hjenglish.com/w/nail\" target=\"_blank\">nail</a> the <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"https://dict.hjenglish.com/w/interview\" target=\"_blank\">interview</a> and get the job&quot; that is how <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"https://dict.hjenglish.com/w/critical\" target=\"_blank\">critical</a> the first 30 seconds are.在面试的时候，你真的只有30秒的时间来建立自我形象。所以这个问题应该是&ldquo;我如何在面试中脱颖而出获得工作&rdquo;，刚开始的那30秒就是有这么重要。</p>\n<p>\n\t<img src=\"http://n1image.hjfile.cn/mh/2017/03/16/17bd00adba4efd3e86f1806e6d2521cb.png\" style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\" /></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">So if you want to nail your introduction and the whole interview follow these steps:所以如果你想让你的自我介绍以及整个面试都让人印象深刻，不妨遵循以下步骤。</span></p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">1. Exercise on the morning of your interview.在面试当天早上进行模拟训练。</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">2. Be presentable.穿着和形象都要得体。</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n\t<img src=\"http://n1image.hjfile.cn/mh/2017/03/20/83d669512af6c54a3b343a7af144fe55.png\" /></p>\n<p>\n\tUse your phone to do a video selfie and check for food in teeth, lipstick on teeth, clumps of mascara etc.先用手机自拍一段视频看看，检查牙齿上有没有菜叶子、口红，看看睫毛膏有没有结块什么的。</p>\n<p>\n\tPeople definitely notice when you are poorly presented and even something small like this can distract the interviewer.如果你的形象准备不充分，人们是真的会留意到的，而且即使是这样细小的细节也会让面试官分心。</p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">3. Arrive in the area early for your pre-game ritual.早点到场做准备活动。</span><br />\n\t</strong></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">A trick I learned in sales was to turn up 20 minutes before my meetings and hang out in the lobby (or one nearby if they don't have one).&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">在销售生涯中我学到过一个小技巧，就是在会议前，我通常会先去大堂逛逛（如果对方那没有，就在附近找一个）。</span></p>\n<p>\n\tIf it was a hot day, I want to cool down so I am not a <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"https://dict.hjenglish.com/w/sweaty\" target=\"_blank\">sweaty</a> disaster. <span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">如果天气很热，我会想找个地方凉快下来，这样就不会让自己变成个满身臭汗的灾难。</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">I also used to bring my headphones and listen to a few songs I like that helped me get into the zone. You will see many athletes doing this which is where I stole the idea from.</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">我还会戴上耳机听几首我喜欢的歌来帮助自己进入状态。你也许看过许多运动员这么干过，我就是从他们那里偷学来的。</span></p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">4. Hit the bathroom before you get to reception.去前台报道之前，先去上厕所。</span><br />\n\t</strong></p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">5. Bring your own water.自己带好水。</span><br />\n\t</strong></p>\n<p>\n\t<img src=\"http://n1image.hjfile.cn/mh/2017/03/16/69c946c85eb00eeb68574aa8285309c2.png\" style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\" /></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">Reception often do not offer you water. The interviewer might but they are often just being polite and don't expect you to say yes.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">前台通常不会提供水。面试官倒是会出于礼貌问下是否要水，但是他们并不希望你真的说&ldquo;要&rdquo;。</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">If the interview is going to go for a while a dry <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"https://dict.hjenglish.com/w/throat\" target=\"_blank\">throat</a> can really start to impact you.</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">如果面试进行得比较长（这通常是好兆头），你的喉咙肯定会干，而这将影响你的发挥。</span></p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">6. Be amazingly nice to everyone.对每个人都要态度非常友好。</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n\t<img src=\"http://n1image.hjfile.cn/mh/2017/03/16/9e18639578f812bc487db79c86c24121.png\" style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\" /></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">I had one sneaky client who used to go out and ask the receptionist how the candidates had acted pre-interview. If he came back with a thumbs down then they would reject the <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"https://dict.hjenglish.com/w/candidate\" target=\"_blank\">candidate</a>.我有一个狡猾的客户，他会出去问前台接待员：应聘者在面试前开始前的态度如何。如果他得到的答案是&ldquo;不好&rdquo;，那么面试官就会拒绝这名应聘者</span></p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">7. Get off your phone.不要玩手机。</span><br />\n\t</strong></p>\n<p>\n\tIf you are waiting in reception or the interview room read your <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"https://dict.hjenglish.com/w/resume\" target=\"_blank\">resume</a> first. If you did not bring it then read a magazine if one is available. <span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">如果你在前台或面试厅中等待，先把你的简历读一下。如果你没带就先读一下杂志。</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">Tapping away on your phone when they arrive can be distracting and some interviewers find it rude (especially the older interviewers).</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">操作手机会让你在面试官到达的时候注意力不集中，而且有些面试官会觉得这很失礼（特别是那些上了年纪的面试官）</span></p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">8. Don't sit with your back to the door in the interview room.在面试厅里，不要背对着门坐。</span><br />\n\t</strong></p>\n<p>\n\t<img src=\"http://n1image.hjfile.cn/mh/2017/03/16/127611c359126423321ceb3d9b9c8e87.png\" style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\" /></p>\n<p>\n\tThis is a caveman trait we have not discarded yet: If you feel your back is unprotected you will naturally be on higher alert and be more uncomfortable. <span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">这是我们从穴居人时代遗留下来的特点，而且至今未摒弃：当你觉得自己的背部不受保护时，你会本能地提高警惕，而且会觉得更加不舒服。</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">Sit where you can see the door. The other side effect of this is the interviewer is facing you and there are less distractions behind you.</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">坐在能看到门的地方。这样做还有个作用就是：面试官在你前面，而你后面不会有东西让你分心。</span></p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">9. Stand when the interviewer enters the room (if you are able).（如果你能站立）就在面试官进来的时候站起来。</span><br />\n\t</strong></p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">10. The introduction.破冰阶段。</span><br />\n\t</strong></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">Nearly always it will be the interviewer who makes the introduction.一般来讲，面试开始时的破冰阶段总是由面试官发起的。</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\"></span><span style=\"line-height: 25.2px;\">A simple response of&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">&quot;Great to meet you X, I am really looking forward to our chat today&quot; is all you need.而你所需要做的回应只是：&ldquo;很高兴见到您XXX，我很期待今天的约谈。&rdquo;</span></p>\n<p>\n\tThen the normal small talk.然后就可以开始正常的寒暄了。</p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>英语君插话：</strong></p>\n<p>\n\tOK，这个quora回答的10步已经讲完了。</p>\n<p>\n\t现在，你已经知道了准备面试所需的心法，只差面试的技术了。</p>\n<p>\n\t而沪江网校正好有这方面的课程哦，英语君给大家筛选出了人气最高的几门，有需求的同学不妨点进去试听以下吧：</p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>首先，</strong>对于还未踏入职场的大学生，你需要的是对招聘市场进行宏观的了解，英语君为你们推荐的是：</p>\n<p>\n\t<a href=\"http://class.hujiang.com/1513043/intro?ch_source=ipo_en_0_rw&amp;editorid=be388e8c\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://n1image.hjfile.cn/mh/2017/03/20/59ea135228dbd137f443245c87c1e49c.jpg\" /></a></p>\n<p>\n\t面试有几种？都有什么流程？不同的面试应该怎样区别对待？面试时哪些话该说哪些话不能说？</p>\n<p>\n\t在踏入职场博弈之前，不妨先花点时间来了解自己面对的到底是什么吧。</p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>第二，</strong>对于想进跨国企业、需要进行英语面试的同学，英语君推荐的是：</p>\n<p>\n\t<a href=\"http://class.hujiang.com/17372889/intro?ch_source=ipo_en_0_rw&amp;editorid=be388e8c\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://n1image.hjfile.cn/mh/2017/06/14/bbef75644c6308e681fe3a604b8ae77a.jpg\" /></a></p>\n<p>\n\t诚然，面试最终需要的是内功，突击面试口语只是表面功夫。</p>\n<p>\n\t但是，不管你的真材实料有多么深厚，面试的时候语塞说不出都是白搭。<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">这门课程能让你在短期内迅速了解各种面试套路、掌握好用的句型和叙事方法。</span></p>\n<p>\n\t真正的实力并不是不用套路，而是知道在什么时候使用套路、什么时候不用。</p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>最后，</strong>单纯挺过面试这一关肯定是不够的，如果你的硬实力不过关，想在一家公司进行长足发展也是不可能的。</p>\n<p>\n\t对于各位想在国际竞争中博得一席之地的同学，英语君推荐：</p>\n<p>\n\t<a href=\"http://class.hujiang.com/17372992/intro?ch_source=ipo_en_0_rw&amp;editorid=be388e8c\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://n1image.hjfile.cn/mh/2017/03/20/fd1643f86da110568aeb0346959d8f0d.jpg\" /></a></p>\n<p>\n\tBEC，又叫&ldquo;剑桥商务英语&rdquo;，是国际职场广泛接受的一个认证考试。</p>\n<p>\n\t通过备考BEC，你能获得直接参与国际会议的能力、进行英语商务谈判、了解商界和职场中的专业概念和表达方式。</p>\n<p>\n\t这对以后的晋升、跨国合作、创业、高阶深造都是非常有用的核心竞争力。</p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n\t好啦，英语君的硬广告就做到这里，希望这篇文章能帮到大家，</p>\n<p>\n\t最后祝各位认真读到这里的同学都能求职顺利、晋升无阻。</p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n\t（翻译：林浔鸥）</p>\n<p style=\"font-size: 12px; color: #999999;\">\n\t声明：本双语文章的中文翻译系沪江英语原创内容，转载请注明出处。中文翻译仅代表译者个人观点，仅供参考。如有不妥之处，欢迎指正。</p>\n<br /><center><a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p1092331/#relate_articles\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_chat.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a> <a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p1092331\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_digg.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a></center><h3 style=\"margin: 10px;\">本周最热文章</h3><ul style=\"margin: 5px 0;\"><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p795424/\">有声双语美文：当一个作家，书写自己的人生</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p1192028/\">我的命是空调给的，快来拜一拜空调之父</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p1191623/\">Quora精选：中国人如何看待西方的茶？</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p1193378/\">权游7：二丫重逢雪原狼，却说“原来不是你”</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p1192502/\">阿里巴巴未能打入世界500强，京东却进了？</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p1193371/\">什么？比伯取消世界巡演，原因竟然是太累了</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p1135543/\">有声双语美文：童真，真是世界上最美的风景</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p1071136/\">有声Quora：餐厅是怎么引诱我们多花钱的？</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p1193011/\">主唱贝宁顿离世，林肯公园巡演全数取消！</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p1192026/\">双语美文：我们渴望与人交流，不仅仅是说话</a></li></ul><div style=\"margin-top: 10px;\">导航:  <a href=\"http://www.hujiang.com/\" style=\"margin: 5px;\" target=\"_black\">沪江网</a>  <a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/\" style=\"margin: 5px;\" target=\"_black\">沪江英语</a>  <a href=\"http://jp.hujiang.com/\" style=\"margin: 5px;\" target=\"_black\">沪江日语</a>  <a href=\"http://fr.hujiang.com/\" style=\"margin: 5px;\" target=\"_black\">沪江法语</a>  <a href=\"http://kr.hujiang.com\" style=\"margin: 5px;\" target=\"_black\">沪江韩语</a></div><hr style=\"border: 0.5px solid gray;\" />", 
